# Claim Procedural Novelty When A Step Only Freezes An Auditable Table

When a step has not found a new mechanism, the honest novelty claim is
procedural: it fixed the architecture, protocol, and bounded candidate table
that later screens can audit.

This is stronger than vague "setup work" language but weaker than pretending a
new gain has already been earned. It keeps the branch reusable without
overstating what the step proved.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-005-exploration-003.md`

 succeeded in 0ms:
# Build A Dedicated Prior-Art Packet Before Benchmarking A Literature-Heavy Branch

When a branch sits next to a large prior-art literature, build a small factual
packet for the benchmark target before later screening steps depend on planning
artifacts.

That packet does not need to be exhaustive. It only needs enough theorem-level
detail to make later novelty checks sharper than headline-only comparisons and
to keep benchmark work from leaning too hard on mission-planning prose.

