# Divergence Stress Form Is Tao-Insufficient Under The Fixed LEI Ledger

Status: `INFERRED`

Within the Step-2 Tao screen for the fixed exact-rewrite audit, the
`divergence / stress form`

`(u . nabla)u = div(u otimes u)`

does not create a new estimate-level gain on the frozen localized LEI target
`I_flux[phi]`.

Its only credible insertion point is the transport side of the same cutoff
term, where one hopes that integrating by parts will lower the effective
cutoff coefficient. But after that integration by parts, the same stress
interaction against `grad phi` returns. The rewrite therefore preserves an
identity-level incompressible packaging without identifying any smaller
coefficient in the unchanged localized ledger.

Under the branch rule, that leaves the candidate classified as
`reject as Tao-insufficient`.

